ukes is only a strategy to avoid getting nuked before you can close the distance and start beating on the caster.  Clear enough yet?<br><br>&quot;It takes far less costly gear to get to 4k buffed then it takes to be able to get max mb for 4k (it doesnt always hit for max to so sure is not the word to use).&quot;<br><br>Epic + crafted hp rings + dwarf quest + various items wont get me much over 2k unbuffed at 60 as a rogue and or to around 3500 with cleric, shaman, ranger hp buffs and I really think in a 1 on 1 comparison the former total is a lot more meaningful.  In a 1 on 1 fight mannaburn even with ghetto gear will basicly always kill me. Fully buffed by 3 different classes I'm still basicly a twitching pile of overcooked meat if I get mannaburned by someone not on a corpse run.<br><br>Regarding miss ratio.<br><br>&quot;Ah, like casters you mean?&quot;<br><br>I was actually talking about the cloth that drops in newbie zones rather than the cloth that drops in saaaay PoG, 2nd floor of hate, dwarf city quest. Idealy your gear when fighting a rogue consists of AC and hp + enough pr to resist poisons. There is no reason why you should run oom fighting a rogue unless you use a lot of resistable nukes on a guy with high fr cr.  I decently equiped caster has enough AC that the miss ratio should be signifigant. This is just how melee dmg works. Only green mobs allow you to hit most of time.<br><br>&quot;You may not know about it, but casters have this skill called meditation that requires sitting. &quot;<br><br>Amazing simply amazing. Thank you for enlightening me boy do I feel dumb here I was assuming that casters were just a bunch of lazy sons of bitches who sat on their asses all day.  Well genius I have a few tips for you...<br><br>-Med with your back to a wall.<br>-Watch the zone list for enemies.<br>-Watch for people comming near that may be hostile.<br>-Go into 3rd person view if it will help you keep watch.<br>-Keep see invis up.<br><br>No c