dReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I am sick and tired of people bitching about mb</span><hr size=1> &quot;First, what is clear is that you are very scared of wizards. What it comes down to is that you cant fight wizards, therefore wizards are unbalanced. I suggest you look closer to yourself if you realy think its that much easier to get spells off then hit in melee. Maybe even try playing caster yourself in pvp against melee some.&quot;<br><br>Incorrect I am very scared of mannaburn.  Not wizards in general. I know how to pvp non mannaburn wizards. A player with a DT key is stupid though.<br><br>&quot;And how does keeping an eye out for enemies dont help you avoid getting hit by mb? Also, walls arent redily availible outside dungueons. And being forced to sit at the zone wall all the time would deffinitly be a dissadvantage.&quot;<br><br>Well when you see the enemy rogue comming you stand up and fight rather than being taken by suprise makes a HUGE difference in pvp especially vs an offensive class like a wizard or rogue either only needs a short time to hurt someone very badly, you don't need to med by a zone wall just sit against one if its handy...like when your indoors.<br><br>&quot;No rogue should be hit by mb if he is paying attention.&quot;<br><br>What a load of bull as stated before...<br><br>You shadowstep and cast boom dead.<br>You get lucky and channel boom dead.<br>You &quot;step into the nuke&quot; and get it off boom dead.<br>You initiate the fight and get it off boom dead.<br>You exploit LoS boom dead.<br><br>&quot;Yes, I would rather compare it to HT myself, but as its the rogue that is posting that mb is totaly unbalanced and rogues are the essence of balance.&quot;<br><br>Mannaburn IS totally unbalanced, death to... err I mean disc HT is pretty unbalanced too but the latter doesnt' justify the former.  Our goal should be a balanced and sane pvp environment.  As far as rogues. Well I don't think we are imbalanced in the slightest.  The only class that can't fight us at all is enc and that is a problem with enc spells not rogue abilities.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujeshuah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeshuah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/10/02 2:37:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I am sick and tired of people bitching about mb</span><hr size=1> haha the troll rogue strikes again.<br><br>lol i found someone more arrogant and annoyingly opinionated than myself.  Aerimus, do you honestly think anyone cares about your blatantly rogue biased views, besides another rogue?  The extent to which you declare something with half-truths in every post is laughable.  I have read insults to you even on your own class's board.<br><br>I do admit you seem to be more informed than the vast majority of people, but that is also your greatest fault, especially when you try to speak in terms of a wizard when it's obvious what you say isn't really what real wizards experience.<br><br>The way you always feel the need to rebut anyone's post about wizard/melee's or *gasp* your precious rogues was amusing at first, but now is just sad. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/10/02 5:23:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I am sick and tired of people bitching about mb</span><hr size=1> What we need is a few people with mannaburn to comment on the situation.<br><br>What we have here is a bunch of disgruntled wizards distressed about the state of pvp in general and their place in it in particular seeing mannaburn as the &quot;fix&quot; the solution to all their problems.  Yes Mr. Wizard you too can now be good at high end pvp! and a cheer is heard throughout the land! Am I right?  But wait verant is going to take it away! It must be because of the whiners.  All those overpowered melees crying to verant. Those golem wand using, backstabbing, /disc killing sons of bitches!  <br><br>We'll guys it's not.  It's being taken away because its overpowered. It's being taken away because it breaks high end pvp.  It's being taken away because of the idiots who mannaburn someone then go afk in the nexus till mannaburn comes back then do it again, then again, then again.  It's being taken away because this is not how pvp is supposed to be.<br><br>Let me tell you something about pvp.  Everyone who doesn't play pvp agressively sucks. Big time.  Because you lose the advantage that initiating the fight and choosing the battlegrounds gives you.  This is nowhere more true than talking about wizards and rogues whose main defense is a very strong offense and how give up versatility for offensive power.  Wizards imo don't suck.  They just suck at defending themselves when they get attacked. They also suck as much indoors as rogues do in open spaces. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 4:06:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I am sick and tired of people bitching about mb</span><hr size=1> Hi, I play a level 60 wiz on RZ, I've been level 60 for a super long time I was like the 5th level 60 wiz on RZ, including those who exploited XP ressed to get 60 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>That being said, I do not have manaburn yet, since I have not been playing much for about 4 months. I can nonetheless comment on what wizard PvP was _before_ manaburn.<br><br>The casting of _any_ regular DD is too random to be of any use. You won't do a dent to anyone with good resists. The only spell that you can cast reliably in PvP are lures. Now the problem with lures is that they are 4.5 second casting. This can be brought down to 4.0 if you have a level 3 CLASS AA ability.<br><br>With a 4.5 casting spell, from the moment a melee with jboots (or even now with run 3) enters casting range and the moment the melee is on me, there is a little over 2 seconds. This is not eevn time to get of a 3.0 normal DD, much less a 4.5 lure without being hit.<br><br>My testing shows that the channeling of a 4.5 second level 60 lure (our only good damage lure) is of about 25% (figure taken against a monk with a T-Staff) after about 2 seconds melle against him.<br><br>That means to do 825 x 0.66 = 519 damage to a melee I need to be on average hit in melee for an equivalent of 4x 2 seconds lets say about 4x 200 damage (I'm being really nice here)<br><br>Also remember that after this I have a melee on my tail, and I need to run from him, and be able to cast yonder _and_ get a good distance yonder, all this without getting hit.<br><br>Does this sound fair for a wiz vs. melee? Does this sound balanced?<br><br>Wiz are very good vs. other int based casters because they do less DPS to us and much less reliably, pets aren't all a problem, except for epic mage pets who do _huge_ damage, with a proc over 200 damage that's hard to resist, but still they can be dealt with.<br><br>The problem in PvP lies with the fact that in general int casters &lt; melee. And that the int casters best pvp weapon is gate. Maybe for Mr. Rogue the best defense is offense, but for the most offensive INT caster class, the best defense, and might I add the best PvP tactic once you are faced with a melee in single combat is gate. Now, I might add that gate is overpowered, because being able to have a clean getaway is a very important advantage, but is there a possibility that this same wizard is going to take down that melee? No.<br><br>Wiz &gt; int casters in PvP<br>Wiz &lt; melee in PvP<br><br>And as a matter of fact with manaburn it's pretty much the same thing. Wizards are single shotting OTHER int casters, not melees, because other casters can't run up to melee range and interrupt you.<br><br>That's in my eyes the greateest problem with MB, it favors wiz vs. other casters, where wiz were balanced, but does not change much to wiz vs. melee. <p>Aurore<HR>~Seekers of Divinity~<BR>Sorceress of <a href=http://www.ralloszek.net>Rallos Zek</a><BR><a href=http://www.progressquest.com><img src=http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~bnguyen/pony.gif></img></a>The Pony with the Pointy Hat.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushimone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shimone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 7:01:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromW